1
00:00:41,719 --> 00:00:42,600
Hurry, hurry, hurry!

2
00:00:42,600 --> 00:00:43,679
They're right on our heels!

3
00:00:43,679 --> 00:00:44,679
Hurry! Hurry up!

4
00:00:45,119 --> 00:00:46,920
Keep moving! Keep moving forward!

5
00:00:52,039 --> 00:00:52,759
Hurry, hurry!

6
00:00:54,560 --> 00:00:55,320
Go!

7
00:00:55,320 --> 00:00:57,200
No, it's too far!

8
00:00:57,280 --> 00:00:58,520
Just go when I tell you to!

9
00:00:58,520 --> 00:00:59,560
Come on, move!

10
00:01:00,039 --> 00:01:01,520
I'll shoot you!

11
00:01:01,719 --> 00:01:02,920
You think you're so great with a gun?

12
00:01:02,920 --> 00:01:03,799
You're bullying us!

13
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:05,200
If he doesn't move, we'll all die!

14
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:05,920
Shut up!

15
00:01:06,120 --> 00:01:07,120
Give me your prey!

16
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:07,879
What for?

17
00:01:07,879 --> 00:01:08,799
Cut the crap!

18
00:01:09,239 --> 00:01:10,480
Hand it over!

19
00:01:10,879 --> 00:01:11,719
Here, Old Chen!

20
00:01:29,959 --> 00:01:31,120
They actually went for it!

21
00:01:31,640 --> 00:01:32,840
Hurry, hurry! Go!

22
00:01:32,840 --> 00:01:33,879
They're right on our heels, hurry!

23
00:01:42,599 --> 00:01:43,159
Old Lu!

24
00:01:44,959 --> 00:01:45,920
My bag! My bag!

25
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:46,799
Forget about the bag!

26
00:01:46,799 --> 00:01:47,560
Hurry up and go!

27
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:48,159
Go!

28
00:01:54,760 --> 00:01:57,000
Hurry up, everyone! I see the shore!

29
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:06,760
There's... there's no path!

30
00:02:07,280 --> 00:02:08,479
There are no more rocks!

31
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:15,879
Made it across!

32
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:17,360
Hurry up! Go, go, go!

33
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:18,520
Shutong, hurry up!

34
00:02:23,479 --> 00:02:23,960
Hurry!

35
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:25,919
Hurry up here! Come on up!

36
00:02:25,960 --> 00:02:26,879
Hurry up, Old Chen!

37
00:02:30,479 --> 00:02:31,159
Shutong!

38
00:02:46,639 --> 00:02:47,479
Hurry, hurry!

39
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:53,159
Dawei, hurry! Be careful!

40
00:03:06,159 --> 00:03:06,960
Give it to me!

41
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:27,800
Lao Liu!

42
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:28,639
Lao Liu!

43
00:03:28,919 --> 00:03:29,759
I got bitten!

44
00:03:30,319 --> 00:03:31,360
Run up! Save me!

45
00:03:32,599 --> 00:03:33,520
Hurry, save me!

46
00:03:33,919 --> 00:03:34,919
Grab onto my pole!

47
00:03:35,159 --> 00:03:35,840
Hurry!

48
00:03:35,919 --> 00:03:38,120
Here! Lao Liu, grab it!

49
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:40,319
Save me!

50
00:03:41,919 --> 00:03:42,599
Lao Liu!

51
00:03:46,039 --> 00:03:46,840
Lao Liu!

52
00:04:28,399 --> 00:04:30,319
What's wrong? Are you okay?

53
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:32,199
I'm fine. Just bumped into something.

54
00:04:40,319 --> 00:04:41,120
That kid...

55
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:43,160
Why did you just...

56
00:04:43,160 --> 00:04:44,920
snatch Lao Liu's prey and run?

57
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:47,560
Couldn't you wait for him?

58
00:04:49,839 --> 00:04:50,680
I thought...

59
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:54,160
he would run over here with me.

60
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:55,680
Does what you thought matter?

61
00:04:56,079 --> 00:04:57,600
If you had waited and given him a hand,

62
00:04:57,800 --> 00:04:58,920
he'd be injured at worst.

63
00:04:59,120 --> 00:05:00,959
Would he have lost his life like this?

64
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:03,800
Brother Pang is right.

65
00:05:06,639 --> 00:05:08,319
But I didn't do it on purpose.

66
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:15,120
Let's figure out a way to leave here quickly.

67
00:05:18,639 --> 00:05:19,519
Stop crying.

68
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:20,920
It's okay, it's okay.

69
00:05:21,720 --> 00:05:22,439
Let's go.

70
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:41,000
Field practice isn't like being in college.

71
00:05:42,839 --> 00:05:43,920
When facing danger,

72
00:05:44,680 --> 00:05:47,959
you could bleed or even die at any moment.

73
00:05:48,959 --> 00:05:50,120
All we can do

74
00:05:50,439 --> 00:05:52,160
is try our best to protect ourselves

75
00:05:52,279 --> 00:05:53,720
and the safety of our companions.

76
00:06:15,240 --> 00:06:16,279
Why is there no path?

77
00:06:18,839 --> 00:06:19,680
It's a dead end.

78
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:25,000
We can't go back either.

79
00:06:26,879 --> 00:06:28,319
Where are we supposed to go?

80
00:06:30,199 --> 00:06:31,000
Listen.

81
00:06:31,879 --> 00:06:33,600
Listen? Listen to what?

82
00:06:38,279 --> 00:06:39,079
The sound of water.

83
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:44,439
Nonsense. Without water, how could there be Miasma Water Stingers?

84
00:06:44,879 --> 00:06:45,399
No.

85
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:24,319
There's light.

86
00:07:26,959 --> 00:07:29,680
The dawn of victory belongs to us after all.

87
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:39,759
We're seeing the light of day again.

88
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:41,519
Where is this?

89
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:58,519
This moss is pretty thick.

90
00:08:01,199 --> 00:08:02,480
And look at this rock wall.

91
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:05,439
It might've been formed by a waterfall over a long time.

92
00:08:05,439 --> 00:08:06,480
This is a waterfall?

93
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:08,319
Where is the waterfall?

94
00:08:08,879 --> 00:08:10,959
When we came in earlier, Brother Liu said

95
00:08:11,319 --> 00:08:12,920
that because the water level in the cave dropped,

96
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:14,120
we couldn't use the bamboo rafts.

97
00:08:14,759 --> 00:08:15,720
Now it seems

98
00:08:15,759 --> 00:08:17,000
it's probably because Ailong Mountain

99
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,079
didn't get enough rainfall.

100
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:19,879
So that caused the upstream of this waterfall

101
00:08:19,879 --> 00:08:20,920
to be unable to gather water,

102
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:22,439
and naturally, there's no water downstream.

103
00:08:22,439 --> 00:08:23,560
Then this riverbed

104
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:25,680
should be the waterway discovered by the herb gatherers.

105
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:27,879
Besides, if this waterway existed,

106
00:08:27,879 --> 00:08:29,000
when building the Dian King's Tomb,

107
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:30,720
they wouldn't have needed to be in Ailong Mountain

108
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:31,879
to dig a canal.

109
00:08:31,959 --> 00:08:34,320
So you're saying the path we took earlier

110
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:36,919
really was the canal dug by the Dian King back then?

111
00:08:37,039 --> 00:08:38,080
It's highly possible.

112
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:40,120
It might be due to crustal movements

113
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:41,799
that the river changed its course in the cave

114
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:42,960
and became a dead end.

115
00:08:43,519 --> 00:08:44,720
Let me summarize.

116
00:08:45,240 --> 00:08:46,799
You guys just said a whole bunch of stuff,

117
00:08:47,159 --> 00:08:48,679
and the main idea is

118
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:50,720
that if we follow this river,

119
00:08:50,919 --> 00:08:52,240
we can find Guyu, right?

120
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:54,080
Master Pang is finally catching on today.

121
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:56,519
Of course. With my wisdom...

122
00:08:57,039 --> 00:08:57,720
Let's go.

123
00:08:58,120 --> 00:08:58,720
Let's go.

124
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:26,320
Commander Chen,

125
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:28,120
what do we do next?

126
00:09:28,960 --> 00:09:30,399
Earlier at the Caiyun Inn,

127
00:09:30,399 --> 00:09:31,360
I used my binoculars

128
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:33,080
to check the situation on Ailong Mountain.

129
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:34,519
But the clouds were too thick,

130
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:35,600
and I couldn't see anything.

131
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:37,600
I thought once we got out of the cave

132
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:39,600
and crossed Ailong Mountain, it would be better.

133
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:40,879
At least we could still

134
00:09:40,879 --> 00:09:42,720
rely on the formation of mountains and rivers

135
00:09:43,039 --> 00:09:45,279
to identify the terrain and set a route.

136
00:09:45,759 --> 00:09:47,559
But the clouds and mist here are too low.

137
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:49,039
I can't see out at all.

138
00:09:49,039 --> 00:09:50,600
Plus, with all these trees and vines,

139
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:51,919
my secret geomancy skills

140
00:09:51,919 --> 00:09:53,080
are pretty much useless.

141
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:00,559
I got it lit!

142
00:10:02,559 --> 00:10:05,360
If we hadn't dropped our tinder in the cave,

143
00:10:05,360 --> 00:10:06,879
would I have to go through all this trouble?

144
00:10:07,399 --> 00:10:08,919
My arm is practically broken.

145
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:10,720
I'm like a primitive man.

146
00:10:14,039 --> 00:10:14,600
Nice.

147
00:10:18,759 --> 00:10:20,080
You're that good, Staff Officer He?

148
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:21,960
How is it?

149
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:23,399
You can try hunting with it later.

150
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:25,159
Not bad.

151
00:10:25,879 --> 00:10:27,080
Looks pretty decent.

152
00:10:28,159 --> 00:10:29,679
Have you guys seen Ding Dawei?

153
00:10:30,279 --> 00:10:31,559
No, what's wrong?

154
00:10:31,759 --> 00:10:33,600
What kind of trouble is that kid causing now?

155
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:35,320
I saw him heading that way earlier.

156
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:36,919
It's been over an hour, and he's not back yet.

157
00:11:02,559 --> 00:11:04,000
Bro, you startled me.

158
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:05,720
What are you doing over there alone?

159
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,120
I'm collecting specimens.

160
00:11:07,399 --> 00:11:08,759
What kind of specimens?

161
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:10,519
Come here. Come take a look.

162
00:11:10,919 --> 00:11:11,759
Be careful.

163
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:13,759
The thorns on that tree next to you are poisonous.

164
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:23,120
Look, this is a needle fern.

165
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:24,559
The leaves of ferns

166
00:11:24,559 --> 00:11:27,240
have both photosynthetic and spore reproduction functions.

167
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:28,399
This needle fern

168
00:11:28,519 --> 00:11:30,799
must have, during its long evolutionary process,

169
00:11:30,799 --> 00:11:33,159
mutated to adapt to the environment.

170
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:34,240
Mutated?

171
00:11:34,240 --> 00:11:34,919
Exactly.

172
00:11:34,919 --> 00:11:36,480
All living organisms in nature

173
00:11:36,480 --> 00:11:37,919
have the potential to mutate,

174
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:38,799
especially under

175
00:11:38,799 --> 00:11:41,320
conditions of a clearly abnormal evolutionary environment.

176
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:42,399
Like the Venus flytrap,

177
00:11:42,840 --> 00:11:44,519
and the Miasma Water Stinger we encountered earlier.

178
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:45,919
This reminds me of

179
00:11:45,919 --> 00:11:47,480
the time researchers

180
00:11:47,519 --> 00:11:49,879
discovered the Yeti crab on the Pacific ocean floor.

181
00:11:50,279 --> 00:11:51,440
Yeti crab?

182
00:11:51,519 --> 00:11:53,320
That's right, the Yeti crab.

183
00:11:53,960 --> 00:11:54,919
The Yeti crab

184
00:11:55,399 --> 00:11:57,200
has no visual function at all.

185
00:11:58,639 --> 00:11:59,440
It

186
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:02,679
is covered in yellow bacterial colonies.

187
00:12:02,720 --> 00:12:04,200
Some researchers believe

188
00:12:04,399 --> 00:12:05,360
these bacterial colonies

189
00:12:05,360 --> 00:12:06,279
are meant to help them

190
00:12:06,279 --> 00:12:09,120
withstand the toxic fluids from volcanic vents.

191
00:12:09,919 --> 00:12:11,480
This is also a mutation

192
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:12,720
that occurred to adapt to the environment.

193
00:12:13,759 --> 00:12:17,320
Look here, the terrain and topography are so peculiar.

194
00:12:17,399 --> 00:12:18,320
If we keep going forward,

195
00:12:18,639 --> 00:12:19,879
who knows how many more

196
00:12:19,879 --> 00:12:21,360
magical creatures we'll discover.

197
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:24,639
Dawei, here's the thing.

198
00:12:25,279 --> 00:12:27,320
Tomorrow we're heading towards Guyu.

199
00:12:27,360 --> 00:12:29,240
What dangers might occur where we're going,

200
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:30,279
no one can say for sure.

201
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:32,799
We won't be taking you with us.

202
00:12:33,279 --> 00:12:33,960
Bro,

203
00:12:34,679 --> 00:12:36,519
didn't we agree to go to Guyu together?

204
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:38,279
I thought about it,

205
00:12:38,879 --> 00:12:39,679
and there's no need to bring you along

206
00:12:39,679 --> 00:12:40,919
to take this risk with us.

207
00:12:40,919 --> 00:12:42,120
You guys are going for archaeology,

208
00:12:42,279 --> 00:12:43,600
and I'm looking for butterflies.

209
00:12:43,679 --> 00:12:45,080
I won't bother you.

210
00:12:45,240 --> 00:12:47,320
Besides, the kind of butterfly I'm looking for

211
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:49,320
is very likely to only appear

212
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:50,480
in places with ancient ruins.

213
00:12:50,679 --> 00:12:52,559
So we might end up in the exact same place.

214
00:12:52,759 --> 00:12:53,919
Even if we separate now,

215
00:12:54,120 --> 00:12:54,840
on the way,

216
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:56,279
we're very likely to run into each other again.

217
00:12:57,480 --> 00:12:59,159
So why can't we go together?

218
00:13:00,639 --> 00:13:02,720
Why do you insist on finding that butterfly?

219
00:13:03,759 --> 00:13:05,279
Is it just because it's rare?

220
00:13:09,639 --> 00:13:11,559
It's indeed not just because it's rare.

221
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:19,720
Do I have to tell you

222
00:13:20,519 --> 00:13:22,080
to be allowed to go with you?

223
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:23,720
It's okay.

224
00:13:24,679 --> 00:13:26,600
If you don't want to say, I won't force you.

225
00:13:33,600 --> 00:13:35,000
Then I'll go pack my things.

226
00:13:35,240 --> 00:13:35,919
Okay.

227
00:13:55,480 --> 00:13:58,639
My father spent his whole life searching for

228
00:13:58,639 --> 00:14:00,120
Kashinfu's Ghost Beauty Butterfly.

229
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:03,320
Seeing this butterfly

230
00:14:04,039 --> 00:14:05,519
was his greatest lifelong wish.

231
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:10,679
I want to help fulfill his dying wish.

232
00:14:29,200 --> 00:14:29,919
Dawei.

233
00:14:46,840 --> 00:14:47,559
Dawei.

234
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:49,000
Here.

235
00:14:49,799 --> 00:14:50,320
Thanks.

236
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:51,120
What are you looking at?

237
00:14:54,240 --> 00:14:54,919
Listen.

238
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:22,440
What kind of tree is this?

239
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:23,919
It's way too big.

240
00:15:25,919 --> 00:15:26,639
Listen, guys.

241
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:41,720
Morse code.

242
00:15:42,080 --> 00:15:42,879
What?

243
00:15:42,919 --> 00:15:44,279
Morse code.

244
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:47,120
It's an international code

245
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:48,080
using only long and short signals.

246
00:15:48,480 --> 00:15:49,200
Listen.

247
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:51,879
Three short, three long, three short.

248
00:15:52,720 --> 00:15:53,600
Translated,

249
00:15:53,960 --> 00:15:55,919
it's the universal distress signal,

250
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:57,240
SOS.

251
00:15:58,240 --> 00:16:00,600
Hold on, Staff Officer He. That's getting creepy.

252
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:01,279
Are you saying

253
00:16:01,279 --> 00:16:03,080
someone in there is asking us for help?

254
00:16:04,519 --> 00:16:05,320
But

255
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:07,120
this sound

256
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:09,039
was rhythmic at first,

257
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:11,159
and then it became chaotic.

258
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:12,679
The sound is too faint.

259
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:14,519
We might have missed a part of it.

260
00:16:14,879 --> 00:16:16,759
We're almost within the perimeter of the Dian King's Tomb.

261
00:16:17,039 --> 00:16:18,000
Any strange occurrences

262
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:19,519
could be related to the Dian King's Tomb.

263
00:16:19,639 --> 00:16:20,559
I'll go up and take a look.

264
00:16:21,159 --> 00:16:22,879
I'll go first. Fatty, guard the tree.

265
00:16:33,080 --> 00:16:34,279
Throw the rope down.

266
00:16:42,919 --> 00:16:44,200
Be careful, Staff Officer He.
